<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880627-0025 </DOCNO><HL> New Securities Issues </HL><SO> </SO><CO> BP F PEP PHG </CO><IN> BON </IN><TEXT>      The following were among yesterday's offerings and pricings in the U.S. and non-U.S. capital markets, with terms and syndicate manager, as compiled by Dow Jones Capital Markets Report:                          CORPORATES   BP America Inc. -- $200 million of 10% guaranteed debentures, due July 1, 2018, was priced at 99.325 to yield 10.071%. The debentures are noncallable for 10 years. The issue was priced at 108 basis points above the rate of the Treasury 8 7/8% issue of 2017. Rated single-A-1 by Moody's Investors Service Inc. and double-A by Standard andamp; Poor's Corp., the issue will be sold through underwriters led by Goldman, Sachs andamp; Co.   Ford Motor Credit Co. -- $200 million of notes, due July 1, 1998, was priced at par to yield 9 3/4%. The notes are noncallable for five years. The issue was priced at 88 basis points above the rate of the Treasury 10-year note. Rated double-A-2 by Moody's and double-A-minus by Sandamp;P, the issue will be sold through underwriters led by Goldman Sachs.                            EUROBONDS   PepsiCo Inc. -- 100 million European currency units of 7 3/8% bonds due Oct. 4, 1992, priced at 101.575 to yield 6.92% at issue price and 7.38% less full fees, via Morgan Stanley International Ltd. Fees 1 5/8.   Alliance andamp; Leicester Building Society (U.K.) -- #125 million of floating-rate notes due July 1993, via J.P. Morgan Securities Ltd. Semi-annual coupon of the higher of one-month London interbank offered rate flat or six-month Libor plus 1/16, reset on a monthly basis, at a price of par.   Osuuspankkien Keskuspankki OY (Finland) -- 10 billion yen of 5% bonds due June 30, 1993, priced at 101 7/8 to yield 4.57% at issue price and 5% less full fees, via IBJ International Ltd. Fees 1 7/8.   N.V. Philips (Netherlands) -- 250 million Swiss francs of 4 3/8% notes due July 15, 1995, priced at par, via Union Bank of Switzerland. Call from July 15, 1992, at 101 1/2, declining by 1/2 a year to par.   Furusato Industries (Japan) -- 30 million Swiss francs of convertible notes due Aug. 31, 1992, indicating a 3/4% coupon at par, via Bank Leu. Call from Aug. 31, 1990, at 104, declining by one point semi-annually to par. Convertible Aug. 2, 1988, through Aug. 17, 1992, at a premium expected to be 5% above the closing share price when terms are fixed by Thursday.</TEXT></DOC>